-- Edison, Monte Paschi, STMicro, UniCredit May Move: Italy Equity Preview
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-07-23T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/edison-monte-paschi-stmicro-unicredit-may-move-italy-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  
 Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB  increased 556.34, or 2.8
percent, to 20,694.26 in Milan.  
 Italy’s biggest banks may move as European lenders publish
the results of stress tests.  UniCredit SpA  (UCG IM) rose 3.1
percent to 2.05 euros;  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA  (ISP IM) climbed 4.8
percent to 2.43 euros;  Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA  (BMPS
IM) gained 4.3 percent to 97.7 cents; Banco Popolare SC (BP IM)
rose 3.5 percent to 4.65 euros; and  Unione di Banche Italiane
SCPA  (UBI IM) increased 2.6 percent to 8.09 euros.  
 Edison SpA (EDN IM): Italy’s second-largest power generator
plans to report first-half results. The stock increased 0.7
percent to 92.1 cents  
 Finmeccanica SpA  (FNC IM),  Eni SpA  (ENI IM): Italian Prime
Minister Silvio Berlusconi and Russian President Dmitry Medvedev
are scheduled to meet in Milan. The two leaders may discuss
defense and energy cooperation.  Finmeccanica , Italy’s biggest
defense company, gained 3.4 percent to 8.75 euros.  Eni , Europe’s
fourth-largest oil company, rose 2.4 percent, to 15.63 euros.  
 STMicroelectronics NV  (STM IM): Europe’s largest chipmaker
plans to hold a conference call on second-quarter results. The
stock advanced 2.3 percent to 6.75 euros.  
